>JD: ENNOSTU 6A TONNE.US +60 415
#note the moment of truth: eschew the bingo, or take my best shot? from my simulation work, I'm thinking this was an error. I can play NEONS at N5 right now to drop his bingo percentage to around 10%; that leaves me with a 63-point advantage and kills the best lane on the board. then, next turn I can block on column D and close all the rest of the lanes on the board! He may still hit a VAGUES bingo, so it's not a sure win, but I think it was a better try than bingoing here. I also thought it was possible that I could outrun a lot of his bingos (I should win if his bingo doesn't hit a TWS) but that may have been too optimistic.
